@startuml
title End-to-End VietQR Payment Demo

actor "Admin / Ops" as Admin
participant "Ops Dashboard\n:4173" as Ops
participant "Gateway API\n:8000" as Gateway
database PostgreSQL as DB
participant "Demo merchant backend\n+ checkout :8100" as Merchant
actor Customer
participant "Customer banking app" as BankApp
participant "Bank/provider simulator" as Provider
participant "Gateway worker" as Worker

Admin -> Ops: Bootstrap first Admin
Admin -> Ops: Create and approve merchant
Ops -> Gateway: Credential, VietQR account, portal user, activate
Gateway -> DB: Persist config and audit evidence

Admin -> Merchant: Enter merchant_id, access_key, secret once
Customer -> Merchant: Create checkout order
Merchant -> Gateway: POST /v1/payments + merchant HMAC
Gateway -> DB: Persist PENDING payment and VietQR evidence
Gateway --> Merchant: qr_reference, qr_content, qr_image_base64
Merchant --> Customer: Display amount, transfer content, QR, countdown

Customer -> BankApp: Scan the VietQR image
note right of BankApp
  Scanning fills bank, account,
  amount, and transfer content.
  It does not call the gateway.
end note

Provider -> Gateway: POST signed provider callback (SUCCESS/FAILED)
Gateway -> DB: Persist callback and final payment state
Gateway -> DB: Create PENDING webhook event
Merchant --> Customer: Bank responded; waiting for gateway webhook

Worker -> DB: Lock and load due webhook
Worker -> Merchant: Signed payment webhook
Merchant -> Merchant: Verify HMAC/timestamp and deduplicate event_id
Merchant --> Worker: HTTP 2xx
Worker -> DB: Store delivery attempt and DELIVERED state
Customer -> Merchant: Poll order every second
Merchant --> Customer: Show SUCCESS, FAILED, or EXPIRED

note over Provider
  The simulator replaces a real bank/provider callback only.
  The generated VietQR itself is scannable by a real banking app.
end note
@enduml
